user_query:
Please read input/profile.json, input/voice_samples.txt, and input/platform_requirements.json. Using that material, write five platform-specific bios in my voice: LinkedIn, speaker introduction, website about page, press kit, and conference program. Integrate my credentials into a narrative (do not list them as bullets). Also generate at least five different opening sentence options with an explanation of what each opening does and which reader/context it suits best. Deliverables:

- Write output/bios.json with this structure:
  {
    "person": { "full_name": string },
    "versions": {
      "linkedin": { "text": string, "word_count": number, "char_count": number },
      "speaker_introduction": { "text": string, "word_count": number, "char_count": number },
      "website_about": { "text": string, "word_count": number, "char_count": number },
      "press_kit": { "text": string, "word_count": number, "char_count": number },
      "conference_program": { "text": string, "word_count": number, "char_count": number }
    },
    "openings": [
      { "sentence": string, "what_it_does": string, "best_for_reader": string },
      ... (at least 5 total)
    ]
  }

For each version, compute word_count as the number of whitespace-separated tokens in text, and char_count as the exact character length of text.

- Write output/README.md listing my full name and the five platform versions included.

Honor every constraint in input/platform_requirements.json, including maximum characters, recommended word ranges, the minimum number of opening options, avoiding name-first openings when specified, and including the required exact phrases in the specified versions.
